<title>Communications Director </title>
<link>https://web3.career/r/=YDM3kDN__wk1uGt</link>
<description><![CDATA[<div class="trix-content"> <p><strong>Communications Director </strong></p> <p><br></p> <p><strong>About This Position </strong></p> <p><br></p> <p>High Vibe PR  is a boutique communications firm for companies and brands that redefine the future of culture and entertainment. We’ve announced the world’s largest gaming fund, placed creators in genre-crossing media, launched numerous Web3 games, and handled the crisis comms for the world’s biggest crypto hack. We are rapidly expanding and are in search of kind comms professionals who believe in ownership, teamwork, and the power of blockchain technology. </p> <p><br></p> <p>We are seeking a <strong>Communications Director</strong>. This is a remote, full-time position. We are digital nomads looking for someone based in CEST and EST time zones only.</p> <p><br></p> <p><strong>Responsibilities: </strong></p> <ul> <li>Provide strategic and tactical PR contributions including drafting press releases, writing pitches, as well as managing media relationships;</li> <li>Work with clients on announcements, evergreen stories, and proactive stories to meet client goals;</li> <li>Collaborate with Founder to support PR activations from concept to execution including planning, project management, execution, and reporting;</li> <li>Identify executive positioning opportunities for clients including speaking engagements and thought leadership moments; </li> <li>Manage administrative tasks such as internal project management, client call notes, monthly recaps, and reporting;</li> <li>Lead weekly client calls and staff interviews, as needed</li> </ul> <p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p> <ul> <li>BA in Communications, Journalism, Marketing, or a related field</li> <li>5-8+ years experience in a comparable PR agency experience</li> <li>Significant record in placing stories in major media outlets </li> <li>Interest in crypto, Web3, NFTs, and gaming</li> <li>Established relationships with press and key industry professionals</li> <li>Strong verbal, written, and interpersonal communication skills</li> <li>Strong organizational and project management skills </li> <li>Native English speaker<br><br> </li> </ul> <p><strong>About High Vibe PR </strong></p> <p>High Vibe PR is a boutique communications firm for companies and brands at the intersection of gaming and entertainment. As a small (but mighty!) team we act as an extension of our clients’ teams and as a trusted advisor. We work with a small number of clients so that we can go deeper with each client and do work that provides incredible value. Our work goes beyond traditional PR to shape stories that create impact and define brands as industry standouts.<br><br></p> <p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p> <ul> <li>In charge of your own destiny. We are a small team - we don’t play politics, aren’t buried in bureaucracy, and have agency over our schedules and location.</li> <li>No assholes. Life is too short to deal with oversized egos. When evaluating clients, we first look at whether the client is someone we want to work with on a daily basis.</li> <li>Supported. Our goal is to empower not only our clients, but also our team members. We recognize and encourage the importance of life outside of the office, and we've fostered a culture where we support one another.</li> </ul> <p><br>If you want to apply, please send a copy of your CV, links to your three most recent media placements, and a cover letter to Tiffany@highvibepr.com with  ‘<strong>Communications Director Role’ </strong>as the subject line.<br><br></p> <p><strong>Salary </strong></p> <p>80-120k USD, depending on experience.</p> <p><br></p> <p><br><br></p> </div> When applying, mention the word CANDYSHOP to show you read the job post completely.]]></description>
<company>High Vibe PR</company>
<location>Remote - EST or CEST timezone only</location>
<tags>pr, non-tech, executive, marketing-communication, remote, blockchain, crypto</tags>
