<description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Blockchain Engineer</strong>⚡</p><p><strong>New York </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Storm2 is currently partnering with a digital-first art network that is changing the landscape of art collection through the power of blockchain technology. Their cutting-edge artwork transaction database allows art collectors, investors, and managers to tokenize physical artworks and incorporate them into traditional financial instruments.</p><br><p>They are looking for a Blockchain Engineer to join their growing team and directly build out the future of art collection by working on their flagship product. This is a unique opportunity to work for a one-of-a-kind company in the space.</p><br><p><strong><u>Responsibilities</u></strong></p><br><ul> <li>Create cutting-edge blockchain apps and decentralized applications (DApps), such as smart contracts, non-fungible tokens (NFTs), and digital certificates.</li> <li>Work with several blockchain platforms and infrastructures, such as Algorand and its SDKs, Polygon, and Avalanche.</li> <li>Oversee and develop all phases of contract development, including requirement collecting, design, development, testing, deployment, and event monitoring.</li> </ul><br><br><p><strong><u>Requirements</u></strong></p><br><ul> <li>4-5 years of professional blockchain engineer experience.</li> <li>Knowledge in creating successful smart contracts using <strong>Solidity</strong>.</li> <li>Practical knowledge of one or more blockchain technologies in a production setting, ideally <strong>Algorand, Ethereum</strong>, and/or <strong>Polygon</strong>.</li> <li>Proficiency in <strong>Python</strong> and/or <strong>Typescript</strong>.</li> <li>Experience with <strong>web3.js</strong>, <strong>ethers.js</strong>, or similar libraries.</li> </ul><br><p><strong><u>Bonus</u></strong></p><ul> <li>Familiarity with REACH</li> <li>Experience with Serverless architecture, AWS Lambda, Azure Functions or similar</li> <li>Experience with financial products or fintech</li> </ul><br><p>Why Apply?</p><ul> <li>Hybrid work schedule opportunities.</li> <li>Social gaming evenings with activities and art exhibitions.</li> <li>Competitive salary and vacation days.</li> </ul><br><br><p><em>🌎New York</em></p> When applying, mention the word CANDYSHOP to show you read the job post completely.]]></description>
